element.name: River Liffey by toczygroszek, Unknown Cache (4.5/1)
element.long-description:
The River Liffey (Irish: An Life) is a major river in Dublin. It begins in Sally Gap in the Wicklow mountains. The length of this river is about 125 km.
The cache is placed close to the Liffey. Coordinates above are for reference only. To get the true coordinates you must find River Tolka and River Dodder cache and obtain information placed on lids of the caches. Use it with the picture below and you will get coordinates for the final cache.
The cache is a small container with some goodies. A new not registered Travel Bug tag is the FTF prize.
You can check your answers for this puzzle on
Geochecker.com.

2009-12-01T20:00:00Z : Write note by toczygroszek
Congratulations to Dara not only for finding this cache, but for #1000 find in my all caches [:D]

2009-12-01T20:00:00Z : Found it by daraconn
I made a night-time visit to this area to find Inexorable and this cache. I was very impressed with how this whole area has changed. Thanks for an excellent series - 3 well-designed, tricky, and enjoyable puzzles.

2009-07-12T19:00:00Z : Found it by Elethiomel
Found today with tolmaion. An excellent trio of caches that we really enjoyed.
TFTC!

2009-07-12T19:00:00Z : Found it by tolmaion
Solved the puzzle late last night after finding River Dodder and River Tolka earlier in the day. But when I went to the coordinates, I could not find anything in the darkness...
I came back during the day today and together with Elethiomel did a thorough search of a wider radius, finally locating the cache about 10m from the GPS coordinates.
In: - Out: -
The three river caches are a great little series with fun riddles. TFTC!
